  "prompt": "What universities does Frontline recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Frontline, like many companies in the technology and education sectors, typically recruits new graduates from a variety of universities, especially those known for strong programs in relevant fields. While I don't have access to specific recruitment data for Frontline, companies in this sector often look for graduates from universities with strong programs in:\n\n1. **Computer Science/Software Engineering**\n2. **Information Technology**\n3. **Data Science/Analytics**\n4. **Education Technology**\n5. **Business Administration (especially with a focus on technology or management)**\n6. **Graphic Design/User Experience (UX)**\n7. **Marketing and Communications (particularly digital marketing)**\n\nFrontline may prioritize candidates with skills in software development, data analysis, and educational methodologies, depending on the specific roles they are hiring for.\n\nTo get the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's best to check Frontline's official career page or reach out to their HR department directly. They may also attend university career fairs or have partnerships with specific schools that can give insight into their typical recruiting targets.",
